Corrugated paperboard is widely applied in packaging design because of its excellent protective performance and energy absorbing capacity (Ge, 2009). The compression stress-strain curve for corrugated paperboard is illustrated in Figure 2, from which we can obtain some general laws as below:


σ(ɛ) is continuous on the whole interval;

The number of the points where stress-strain function derivative equals to 0 depends on the layer of the corrugated paperboard, to be specific, the n-layer corrugated paperboard has 2n points with stress-strain function derivative equaling to 0;

σ(ɛ)>0, when 0<ɛ<ɛb, while σ(0)=0;

σ(ɛ)=Eɛ, when 0<ɛ<ɛL, where E is the initial elasticity modulus of corrugated paperboard.

Figure 2.
Typical compression stress-strain curve of corrugated paperboard.
